The paper deals with the complexity of a communication game, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The game involves manipulating and transmitting data, which suggests a connection to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The authors also mention graph theory (cs.GT) in their introduction as a related area of study. Finally, the game involves finding optimal strategies, which could be seen as a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG).
